  "title": "Tapping for peace around paying bills",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute script for shifting bills from dread to neutral.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 7 of MONEY: A 12-Week Tapping Program. The script targets the tension that comes with bills arriving and being paid: the dread of opening the post, the resentment of money going out, the belief that bills and struggle are the same thing. Use before a regular bill-payment session.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 7 of MONEY: A 12-Week Tapping Program (Rebecca J Page, 2025), \"Invite peace around paying bills.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
